HEADWORD: Excarnificate
<hw>Ex*car"ni*fi*cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ex</ets> out + LL. <ets>carnificatus</ets>, p. p.
<ets>carnificare</ets> to carnify; cf. L. <ets>excarnificare</ets> to
tear to pieces, torment. See <er>Carnify</er>.]</ety> <def>To clear of
flesh; to excarnate.</def> <rj><au>Dr. H. More.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

